---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1>About Open edX Plugins Browser</h1>

  <section class="about-content">
    <h2>What is this?</h2>
    <p>
      The Open edX Plugins Browser is an automatically-updated catalog of all frontend plugin
      slots available across Open edX's ecosystem of Micro-Frontend Applications (MFEs).
    </p>

    <h2>Why does this exist?</h2>
    <p>
      Open edX has adopted a plugin-based architecture for frontend customization using the
      <strong>Frontend Plugin Framework (FPF)</strong>. This allows site operators and developers
      to extend and customize MFEs without forking the codebase.
    </p>

    <p>
      However, discovering what plugin slots are available and what they do required manually
      browsing GitHub repositories. This browser centralizes that information in one place.
    </p>

    <h2>How does it work?</h2>
    <p>
      This site automatically collects data from the Open edX GitHub organization every day:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>GitHub Actions runs a scheduled task to fetch all frontend repositories</li>
      <li>For each repository, it looks for a <code>/src/plugin-slots</code> directory</li>
      <li>Plugin slot metadata is extracted from README files and TypeScript definitions</li>
      <li>Data is stored in JSON and committed to this repository</li>
      <li>Astro generates static HTML from that data</li>
      <li>The site is deployed to GitHub Pages</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>What can I do with this information?</h2>
    <p>
      You can use the plugin slot information to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Understand what customization points are available in each MFE</li>
      <li>See what properties and operations each slot supports</li>
      <li>Find the source code for each plugin slot</li>
      <li>Integrate your custom plugins into Open edX</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How do I use plugin slots?</h2>
    <p>
      For detailed instructions on using plugin slots, see the
      <a href="https://docs.openedx.org/en/latest/site_ops/how-tos/use-frontend-plugin-slots.html"
        target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Open edX documentation on Frontend Plugin Slots
      </a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What about the data?</h2>
    <p>
      All data in this browser is automatically collected from publicly available Open edX
      repositories. The source code for this browser is also open source and available on
      <a href="https://github.com/tecoholic/openedx-plugins-browser" target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Is something missing or wrong?</h2>
    <p>
      If you notice missing data or incorrect information, please:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Check that the plugin slots are properly documented in the MFE's
        <code>/src/plugin-slots</code> directory
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/openedx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Open an issue in the relevant Open edX repository
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Or open an issue in
        <a href="https://github.com/tecoholic/openedx-plugins-browser/issues" target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">this browser's repository</a>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #555;
  }

  .about-content ol,
  .about-content ul {
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #555;
  }

  .about-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about-content a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .about-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  code {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
